<body>
    <header>
        <h1><marquee height="45">Kung Pao Chicken</marquee></h1>
    </header>

    <section>
        <h2>Ingredients</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>1 pound boneless, skinless chicken breasts, cut into bite-sized pieces</li>
            <li>2 tablespoons soy sauce</li>
            <li>1 tablespoon rice vinegar</li>
            <li>1 tablespoon hoisin sauce</li>
            <li>1 tablespoon cornstarch</li>
            <li>2 tablespoons vegetable oil</li>
            <li>3/4 cup unsalted dry roasted peanuts</li>
            <li>3 cloves garlic, minced</li>
            <li>1 tablespoon grated ginger</li>
            <li>1/2 cup diced red bell pepper</li>
            <li>1/2 cup diced green bell pepper</li>
            <li>2 green onions, sliced</li>
            <li>1 tablespoon sesame oil</li>
            <li>1 teaspoon red pepper flakes (optional, for extra heat)</li>
            <li>Cooked white rice for serving</li>
        </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h2>Tags</h2>
        <ol>
            <li>Chinese</li>
            <li>Spicy</li>
            <li>Main Dish</li>
        </ol>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h2>Instructions</h2>
        <ol>
            <li>In a bowl, mix soy sauce, rice vinegar, hoisin sauce, and cornstarch. Add chicken pieces and toss to coat. Let it marinate for at least 15 minutes.</li>
            <li>Heat vegetable oil in a wok or large skillet over medium-high heat. Add marinated chicken and cook until browned and cooked through. Remove chicken from the pan and set aside.</li>
            <li>In the same pan, add more oil if needed. Add minced garlic and grated ginger, and saut√© until fragrant.</li>
            <li>Add diced red and green bell peppers to the pan and stir-fry until they are tender-crisp.</li>
            <li>Return the cooked chicken to the pan, along with sliced green onions and peanuts. Toss everything together.</li>
            <li>Drizzle sesame oil over the Kung Pao Chicken and sprinkle with red pepper flakes if desired. Toss once more to combine.</li>
            <li>Serve over cooked white rice.</li>
            <li>Enjoy your flavorful Kung Pao Chicken!</li>
        </ol>
    </section>

